================================================================================
Project history
================================================================================

This project was initially named "AgentStack" (specification v1.0 written in
French, preserved as docs/AgentStack_Cahier_des_charges.docx for historical
reference). It was renamed "Praxis" in April 2026, then renamed definitively
to "Colber" on 2026-05-01.

Repository: https://github.com/Obi49/Colber
Domain:     https://colber.dev

================================================================================
Future module licensing
================================================================================

The following modules are released under Apache-2.0 alongside the rest of the
codebase today, but may transition to a separate commercial license once their
production-grade variants are released:

  - apps/insurance/          (when on-chain Solidity contracts ship — step 7b)
  - apps/reputation/         (when scoring v2 with anti-Sybil ships — step 3)

Any such transition will only apply to *new* releases; previously published
versions will remain available under Apache-2.0.

================================================================================
Third-party software
================================================================================

This product depends on third-party libraries listed in package.json files.
Their respective licenses are included in node_modules/<package>/LICENSE
after `pnpm install`. Notable runtime dependencies include:

  - @noble/ed25519           (MIT)        — Ed25519 signatures
  - fastify                  (MIT)        — HTTP framework
  - drizzle-orm              (Apache-2.0) — Postgres ORM
  - postgres                 (Unlicense)  — Postgres driver
  - @grpc/grpc-js            (Apache-2.0) — gRPC server
  - @qdrant/js-client-rest   (Apache-2.0) — Qdrant client
  - pino                     (MIT)        — Structured logging
  - zod                      (MIT)        — Schema validation

For the complete list, run `pnpm licenses list` at the repository root.
